# Comprehensive Guide to VRP-RL Codebase

This document provides a detailed breakdown of the Vehicle Routing Problem (VRP) Reinforcement Learning codebase, explaining the architecture, the training process, and providing explicit instructions on how to modify the code for future experiments.

---

## 1. High-Level Architecture
The codebase separates the task environments (TSP/VRP) from the core Reinforcement Learning (RL) model. 
* **[main.py](file:///c:/COLLEGE/SEM%20X/WORK/VRP-RL_2018/main.py)**: The entry point. Handles arguments matching, environment loading, agent initialization, and the main training loop.
* **[configs.py](file:///c:/COLLEGE/SEM%20X/WORK/VRP-RL_2018/configs.py)**: Manages all hyperparameters and command-line arguments.
* **[VRP/vrp_utils.py](file:///c:/COLLEGE/SEM%20X/WORK/VRP-RL_2018/VRP/vrp_utils.py)**: Contains the core logic for the Vehicle Routing Problem (Environment, State representation, Constraints/Masking, and Reward Function).
* **[model/attention_agent.py](file:///c:/COLLEGE/SEM%20X/WORK/VRP-RL_2018/model/attention_agent.py)**: The neural network brain. It maps out the Actor (Encoder-Decoder) and the Critic, handling graph building and loss computations.
* **`rl_algorithms/`**: Contains modular implementations of the RL loss functions, like REINFORCE and A2C.

